# Content File Rules

When editing files in `src/content/`:

## Frontmatter rules

### Posts (`src/content/posts/`)

Required fields:
- `title`: string, max 80 chars, human-readable
- `date`: YYYY-MM-DD format (today's date for new posts)

Optional but recommended:
- `description`: 1-2 sentences, max 160 chars, for SEO meta and feed excerpts
- `tldr`: one-sentence summary rendered as a TL;DR blockquote and used when `description` is absent
- `faq`: array of `{ q, a }` objects for pillar posts — renders FAQ section and FAQPage JSON-LD
- `tags`: array of lowercase kebab-case strings
- `draft: true` for unpublished posts

Never invent or guess:
- Do NOT make up dates
- Do NOT add `originalUrl` unless you know the actual old URL
- Do NOT add `canonical` unless the content genuinely lives elsewhere first

### Notes (`src/content/notes/`)

Required: `title`, `date`

## Writing style

The single source of truth for voice and thinking is **`docs/voice.md`** — read it before drafting or editing content. It covers TC's voice fingerprint, mechanical rules, the anti-AI-isms blacklist, the phrase bank, thinking style, epistemic standards, and the collaboration protocol (expand a skeleton, then confirm gaps before filling — don't silently omit or invent). Do not duplicate that guidance here.

Mechanical basics that stay in this rule because they're formatting, not voice:
- Code blocks should use fenced backticks with language identifier
- Chinese phrases are fine if they add real context (per the register cards in `docs/voice.md`)

## GEO conventions

See `docs/plans/geo.md` for the full plan. When writing posts:

- Open with a 40–60 word answer capsule (definition-lead first paragraph)
- Each `##` section opens with a self-contained 40–100 word paragraph
- Long-form posts: one hyperlinked primary-source citation per ~150–200 words
- Pillar posts: add 5–7 `faq` items in frontmatter
- Refresh `updated:` quarterly on evergreen content

## File naming

Files MUST be named: `YYYY-MM-DD-kebab-case-slug.md`
- Example: `2026-05-06-my-post-title.md`
- NO spaces, NO uppercase, NO special characters except hyphens

## Validation

After editing, run:
```
npm run check:content
```
